{"id":"psw-spk","title":"Bug: desktop renaming broken â€” missing Wayland rename handler","description":"## Problem
Renaming virtual desktops no longer works. Changes made in KDE System Settings are silently ignored.

## Root Cause
In `setVirtualDesktopManagement()` (virtualdesktops.cpp:44), the `createPlasmaVirtualDesktop` lambda is missing the connection from `PlasmaVirtualDesktopInterface` rename signal back to `VirtualDesktop::setName()`.

Current connections (line 55-65):
```cpp
// KWin â†’ Wayland (outbound only):
connect(desktop, &VirtualDesktop::nameChanged, pvd, [desktop, pvd] {
    pvd->setName(desktop->name());
    pvd->sendDone();
});
// Wayland â†’ KWin (activate only):
connect(pvd, &PlasmaVirtualDesktopInterface::activateRequested, this, [this, desktop] {
    setCurrent(desktop);
});
```

Missing connection (should be added):
```cpp
// Wayland â†’ KWin (rename):
connect(pvd, &PlasmaVirtualDesktopInterface::nameChanged, desktop,
    [desktop](const QString &name) {
        desktop->setName(name);
    }
);
```

Note: Check the exact signal name in KWaylandServer::PlasmaVirtualDesktopInterface â€” it may be `requestSetName`, `nameRequested`, or similar depending on the KWaylandServer version.

## Secondary Issue
Our new `setSpatialNeighbor()` and `setSpatialMode()` methods call `save()` which writes full desktop state (including names) to kwinrc + `group.sync()`. This can race with external config file modifications (e.g., from kcm writing names before KWin reloads).

## Fix
1. Add the missing Wayland rename handler connection in the `createPlasmaVirtualDesktop` lambda
2. After `desktop->setName()`, call `save()` to persist the rename to kwinrc

## Key Files
- src/virtualdesktops.cpp (setVirtualDesktopManagement at line 44, createPlasmaVirtualDesktop lambda)
- KWaylandServer/plasmavirtualdesktop_interface.h (check available signals)

